{"type":"text","timestamp":1781081453324,"sessionID":"ses_14f4721b7ffe9YqMpy2w7P8vI4","part":{"id":"prt_eb0b9fb16001RF7tv00jsnQ0k5","messageID":"msg_eb0b9ea1e001K65cc9dPUH5QVQ","sessionID":"ses_14f4721b7ffe9YqMpy2w7P8vI4","type":"text","text":"No .dockerignore, no .gitignore. Now I have enough to evaluate.\n\nKey observations:\n\n**Dockerfile**: Uses `python:3.11-slim`. Installs: build-essential, gcc, g++, make, tmux, strace, ca-certificates, curl, git, bc, pkg-config, openssl, file. Cleans apt cache. Then installs Rust toolchain.\n- `build-essential` already brings gcc, g++, make → gcc/g++/make are redundant\n- `bc` is not used in test.sh (only arithmetic via shell `$((...))`)\n- `pkg-config` is used by Rust crates that link C libs — probably not needed for a pure-Rust ls but commonly required by many crates; defensible\n- `git` and `tmux` are Harbor hard rules\n- `strace` needed for verifier\n- `openssl`, `file` used by test.sh\n- `curl`, `ca-certificates` used to install rustup\n\n**solution/**: Just `solve.sh`, clean.\n\n**test.sh**: \n- Locks /logs/verifier ✓\n- `unset LD_PRELOAD ...` — given hardened isolation (agent is non-root), agent CAN'T set system loader files but COULD set env vars in its own shell that wouldn't propagate to verifier anyway since test.sh runs as root in a fresh exec. The `unset` is mostly defensive/redundant but cheap.\n- `pkill -u agent` — useful belt-and-suspenders before strace runs.\n- Static workspace grep checks (oracle path, .test_data, oracle.enc, decryption key, reward.txt, uutils, ls_backup, dir/vdir) — these are task-specific anti-cheats, sensible.\n- Oracle hash equality check — sensible (prevents byte-for-byte oracle copy).\n- The 2-phase strace pattern (oracle root, agent under strace) is the documented hardened pattern.\n\n**git_hygiene**: No file > 30MB.\n\n**workspace_clean**: No .gitignore exists. `qa-logs/` and `results/` are present but excluded per rules. The `environment/workspace/examples/` only has a README — no stale code. The `ANTI_CHEAT.md` at the root is a meta-doc — it's not in environment/ so won't be COPYd to /app. It's harmless meta-documentation for task authors. README.md is fine.\n\nPossible redundancies:\n- Dockerfile: `gcc g++ make` redundant with `build-essential`\n- Dockerfile: `bc` — let me verify it's truly unused","time":{"start":1781081438998,"end":1781081453311}}}
